      "writtenOn": "2019-05-02T17:40:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Maybe we should fail earlier than this? Like when we created the SkMultiSkpWriter? That way we don\u0027t waste a bunch of time serializing when there\u0027s no place to save it.\n\nI\u0027d suggest making this class use a factory instead of a public constructor. The creation would look something like:\n\n  std::unique_ptr\u003cSkMultiSkpWriter\u003e SkMultiSkpWriter::Make(int frames, SkString filename) {\n      auto stream \u003d new SkFILEWStream(filename.c_str());\n      if (!stream-\u003eisValid()) {\n          return nullptr;\n      }\n\n      return new SkMultiSkpWriter(frames, std::move(stream));\n  }",
      "range": {
